    <briefdescription>
<para>Request and Response for firewall owner change. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>fwl_id</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Firewall ID in question </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>region</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Region or channel number to set config info This field is unused in case of a simple firewall and must be initialized to zero. In case of a region based firewall, this field indicates the region in question. (index starting from 0) In case of a channel based firewall, this field indicates the channel in question (index starting from 0) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n_permission_regs</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Number of permission registers &lt;= 3 </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>control</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Control register value for this region </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>owner_index</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>New owner index to change to. Owner indexes are setup in DMSC firmware boot configuration data </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>owner_privid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>New owner priv-id, used to lookup owner_index is not known, must be set to zero otherwise </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>owner_permission_bits</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>New owner permission bits </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
